Nov 26 2009 	strong perfume smell pervasive throughout property	I did not stay at the hotel but have been there for both the phantom show last year and last night the blue man group show. Both times I notice a strong perfume smell that hits you as you walk into the property from the parking garage. It seems to be coming directly out of the ventilation system and is pervasive throughout the entire property. It is stuck in my clothes after we leave, like cigarette smoke. It's a pretty hotel and casino and we would have liked to walk around more but the smell in this place makes me nauseous. Frankly I'd much rather deal with lingering cigarette smell than this awful perfume smell. Someone should tell the management to stop with the perfume. Other properties I have visited on the strip do not do this (Bellagio, Palms, Mirage, Mandalay Bay). If you are allergic to perfume or just do not like the smell please think again before booking at this property. We had dinner along the grand canal so we spent several hours in the property and now my clothes smell of the perfume.	
