red that we could see the Red Rock Canyon from our hotel room (with binoculars).Saw Jersey Boys first night. Great Show. Advice here: NEVER NEVER NEVER see a show on your first night, especially if you fly in from East Coast.Saw Cirque de Soleil &quot;O&quot;. It was beyond words. This was my fifth or so Cirque show, so I know what to expect. It was absolutely incredible. Hint: buy a limited view seat and saw money....view is not bad at all.Continental Airlines: Flight going back home. I paid $6 to watch TV. Yes, $6 to watch the shows that you normally would get for free, plus the movie I was suppopsed to get for free. It is all tied in with Direct TV which I didn't want. But, I am really bad flying, so I swiped my credit card and watched stuff that I should have gotten for free. When I went to the regular Direct TV shows, they were LOADED and I mean LOADED with commercials....What the heck??? Why should they take my $6 to make me watch commercials? ARe they kidding.Bad, bad continental airlines. Oh, yea, and thanks for the cold cereal on a 7:30am flight. Just what people want, cold cereal. Are you crazy? At least give us a cold bagel.....or something but cereal?That's it. Great trip. Other couples we went with are thinking about going again next year. My convention is in November, but they want to go early like September or so to get pool weather (Oh yea, by the way, it was a bit chilly in Vegas November 10-15th....defintely not pool weather)	
