Nov 20 2009 	Awesome!	We have been to Las Vegas several times and have stayed in many of the hotels on the strip. The Venetian is always the one we come back to. The suites are great, the service couldn't be better, the location of all of the amenities in the hotel are convenient and the restaurants are wonderful.We usually get offers from the hotel so we don't have to wait in line for check in so if there is a way to book this it seems much better than waiting in the long line at the front desk. Otherwise I would check in at an off hour or just leave your bags with the bellhops at valet and go in have a gelato or shop around and check in later at your convenience. Also, the suites can be a bit of a walk from the elevators so you might want to try and ask for a suite as close to the elevator as possible. I have never had a bad meal at this hotel. I have had perhaps one of the best meals of my life at Aquaknox which is close to the main casino. Delmonico's, Zefferino's and Canallettos are all wonderful. Cafe du Lux is also great for an almost any time meal. The sandwich shop near the main casino has one of the best tuna sandwiches ever. The gelato is perfect... except it does close fairly early for Vegas time.Canyon Ranch Spa is nice but a bit of a walk... like most things in Vegas. I've had a very good hair cut there and a very informative (maybe too much) pedicurist who taught me quite a lot about callouses. The Phantom of the Opera production was very impressive and well worth seeing even if you have seen it before. Other shows worth seeing are Le Reve, Ka and other Cirque shows. However, I would definitely stay away from Chris Angel's show... can't even remember the name of it and am trying to forget the rest of it. The casino offers a wide range of slots and table play. However, the minimums are usually a bit higher but you do get a bit more of a personalized service from the dealers here even if you aren't playing with big bucks. They seem to pay more attention and if you are a bit glassy-eyed in the early morning this can really help.All in all a great place to stay...	
