Oct 17 2009 	Happy with our stay...but the smell has to go!	Got a pretty decent deal with air and hotel through WestJet. Check in guy was nice and although there was a line, we only waited about 5-10 minutes. Said he'd give us a room with a view if we &quot;took care of him&quot; aka gave him some money. My boyfriend slipped him a $20. I've heard that none of the rooms have a good view of the Strip. Our &quot;view&quot; on the 23rd floor had mountains in the background, view of the pool, Treasure Island and an eyesore construction site between us and the mountains. I'm sure it'll be much nicer once the construction is finished. It was our first time staying there, so I can't really comment on the other views you could get. I know a lot of people complain about the distance to get to the rooms. I think this is especially true if you stay in the Venezia tower. To get to our room we had to go through the casino, up an elevator and down a corridor. Probably took us about 5 minutes to walk from the front door to the room. Not bad if you're healthy and don't mind walking, but I don't think my parents would love it. The hotel provides an ironing board and hair dryer, but no coffee maker. Everything costs extra in this hotel (mini fridge, internet, local phone calls). Don't touch anything at the bar by the TV unless you want to buy it. A bottle of water is $7. We did end up getting room service for one night. Just ordered some comfort food (French onion soup, mozza sticks, and mashed potatoes) and the bill came to $40 with tip. The Grand Lux Cafe downstairs is a good place to eat. Just so you know, nothing that tastes decent is cheap on the Strip, although there are plenty of fast food type options around. Grand Lux Cafe has a breakfast buffet for about $15 and the rest of their food looked great. If I stay at the Venetian again, I'll probably eat there every day. For snacks and water I'd go to Walgreens right beside the Venetian. For liquor, if you walk or take The Deuce towards the Stratosphere tower on the Strip there's a cheap liquor store about half a mile down. To keep our things cool, we just filled one of the sinks in our bathroom up with ice. Perfect, and way cheaper than renting a fridge! As others have said, the strong perfume smell is pretty nasty and permeates the lobby and casino. Luckily, I didn't have the strong smell in my hotel room.If you're the type of person who likes to hang out in your hotel room and relax for a portion of your trip, I'd recommend the Venetian. If you want to gamble at the different Casino's on the strip all the time and won't be in your room for long, maybe a different hotel would be better and cheaper for you. Overall, we were happy with our stay and liked the service. I wouldn't say the staff really went above and beyond, but everyone was helpful and friendly enough. I feel like I got what I paid for.	
