Oct 15 2009 	Enjoyed our stay at the Venetian	We stayed at the Venetian Oct 6 to 10, 2009. We had a luxury suite with the most comfortable king bed, which is actually their lead in room. It was very large and very comfortable. Huge bathroom with seperate shower, bathtub, double sinks, vanity table, Sunken living room with sofa (sofa looked very worn - I was a bit surprised at this) and a small dining table with chairs and a nice size desk. We arrived several hours prior to check in and we were able to get our room without a problem and I found the front desk staff to be quite friendly. A view of the strip was offered to us at an additional cost, we decided to forgo the view and we ended up with a view of the pool which was fine. On arrival in our room we realized that many of the numbers on the safe were not working. Maintenance was sent quickly to our room to replace it. The location of the hotel on the strip is excellent , right across from Treasure Island and Mirage. The hotel is huge, with many corridors and it is easy to get disoriented. There is a strong perfume scent that is sprayed in the lobby, this can be very overwhelming and not reccommended if you have allergies.The Grand Canal shops are expensive but nice, there is a food court in amongst the shops with very reasonable meals (the noodle place is great) We ate at the Canalletto Restaurant in the shops area, it was pricey but the food was good (especially the Apple Crepes with green apple sorbet and caramel....mmmm)There is also a food court/cafe area within the hotel, the sandwiches were wonderful and the gelato at Cocolini is a must try!! The most flavours I have ever seen!!There is a small breakfast buffet (small but adequate) My only issues with this hotel were the following: You must use the latch on the door, as housekeeping is opening your door as they knock on it. You have no time to answer them before they are in your room - use the latch!!If you are playing at their Casino, be prepared to wait a while for a drink - a few times we had to pay for drinks at the barThere is no where to print up a boarding pass, you must get concierge to do it or pay for the internet in your room Overall we enjoyed our stay at this hotel , and Vegas is a must visit!! You must do the buffet at the Bellagio, if you can try to do the Champagne brunch at the Bellagio on Saturdays and Sundays - worth the money - tons of selection If you can try to see a show while there, until October 31st Cirque has specials on their official website , you buy one ticket you get the 2nd for $25.00. We saw &quot;O&quot; and absolutely loved it	
