Oct 14 2009 	Gorgeous hotel...only one or two grumbles	The Venetian hotel is amazing- one of the nicest hotels on the Strip by far. We checked in at around 10.00pm so there were no big queues and we were dealt with relatively quickly.Our suite was in the Venezia tower on Floor 4 - facing the back end of the building so needless to say - NO VIEW! But as we were going to get charged $50 a night more for a strip view - decided that this money would be better spent on enjoying ourselves. It can also take a while to walk to the rooms from the Venetian (2 elevators and countless corridors) so it would not be suitable for someone with limited mobility.The suites are gorgeous and the hotel restaurants are great. Its location on the strip is brilliant - it is almost in the middle so nothing is that far away. Better choice than going for something at one end of the strip!My only slight grumble is that in a hotel so big, the service is very impersonal. You do get the impression that individual customer service is not that important and your problems are not dealt with as efficiently as you would like. The door knob on our door broke we we returned from shopping - on our way back out to the theatre and although we were in a rush, it took 2 phone calls (from the lobby) and about half an hour before the maintenance man arrived. And not even an apology - nothing!!That being said, Vegas is amazing! I would definitely like to go back as there is so much to do.. The Phantom at the Venetian is worth seeing but if you have to choose one show - see LOVE by Cirque de Soleil - amazing!	
