Oct 13 2009 	Enjoyed Our Stay	I stayed at the Venetian Oct 9-12/09 in the Venezia tower room 11-517, which had a view of the pool. There were 4 of us in a 2 queen-bed suite, which had a sunken seating area. It was very spacious, 700 sq ft. The bathroom is a very good size with a water closet (with a phone in it) and a double sink vanity area. There is a makeup table with a nice lighted mirror and a blow dryer. The tub and separate shower are both spacious, and there is good water pressure in the shower. We had plenty of towels &amp; facecloths. But the basic amenities were somewhat lacking, such as soap, we only had one cake of soap, one very small bottle of shampoo, conditioner, shower gel, and hand cream. There was no shaving gel or mouthwash provided. Also, they did not provide a laundry bag for dirty clothes as every other hotel that I have ever stayed in does. We had to request to have robes sent to our room as there weren't any upon arrival. They advertise the robes as &quot;plush&quot;, but they are anything but that. Overall, the room was for the most part clean, but just not up to the standard of what I was expecting for such an opulent hotel.There was a minibar, but no fridge or coffee maker. The prices of the minibar items can be called nothing short of highway robbery ($26 for a 500ml bottle of white wine). We did find that the price of wine in the gift shops was not too bad though, so you might want buy it there instead, just be sure to also buy a cork screw as one is not provided in the room.There are many restaurants to choose from, but we only tried Grand Lux Cafe and Tintorreto Bakery. We were very happy with both, the service was excellent, the food very good, and the prices were reasonable. The dinners at the Grand Lux are VERY generous, 2 of us shared 1 meal quite easily. The desserts were HUGE! The 4 of us could not finish the chocolate cake that we ordered.The property is massive (the biggest in Vegas) &amp; it is at times very confusing to navigate, better signage would definitely help. The grounds are absolutely beautiful and there are many pools to choose from (I lost count as to how many exactly).We had no problem with checkin or checkout, it was quick and the staff were pleasant &amp; accomodating. Room service was very good &amp; the wait time was minimal. The food we had, pizza and chicken quesadilla, was very good, but not cheap. Also be warned that if you choose to order drinks at the pools, it will end up costing close to $20/drink.I probably would not stay here again simply because the hotel is just too big for my tastes and it takes too long to get anywhere on the property, but it is a very beautiful hotel.	
