etian was supposed to be a little more high end then some of the other resorts...their shopping, restaurants, etc., was no more pricier then anywhere else (and we checked out a lot of other resorts). OK, I do have one negative, The Venetian pumps in fresh air into their resort, as do all of the resorts, except the Venetian's air was scented. When you first walk into the resort you think &quot;Wow, it smells great in here!&quot;. But after five minutes you are overwhelmed with the very perfume-y smell. Everytime we left our room, our noses was assaulted by the strong, perfume air and after a while it bothered our sinuses and eyes. Some may have enjoyed it, but I found it to be overpowering. The good thing was that it wasn't inside your suite, nor inside the restaurants or shopping mall, so there were places you could retreat to if you didn't want to deal with smelling it.Overall, I would recommend everyone to stay in the Venetian at least once....and it is a must if you are traveling with a large group and you all want to stay in the same room because the rooms are way roomier than any of the other resorts. And eat at Tao and party at Tao....it was awesome!	
