Oct 8 2009 	Beautiful room great price and location	We definitely got a great deal using one of the hotel packages they offered. The hotel is huge, plenty of restaurants(Grand Luxe Café, Delmonico Steakhouse, WolfGang,Dos Caminos,B&amp;B etc.). You can't go hungry with so many varieties. The location is centralized as well. You can walk to Harrah's and catch the shuttle to Paris,MGM. The Fashion Mall across the street has a bus stop to Downtown Freemont. The hotel also has Walgreens, Madame Tussaud Wax Museum, Blue Man group, Indoor/Outdoor Gondola rides. The Suites are spacious, plenty of room to spread around. Downside not enough closet space if you are taking the children with you. There are 3 pools. They are beautiful and you can certainly rent one of the Cabanas. However, someone forgot to consider the location and height of the hotel with regards to the pool. The pool area was mostly covered in shade because the hotel is blocking most of it. So if you wanted to sunbathe, get there early to get the sunny spot. If you like to go to the Spa it is located in the Palazzo. They do have a fitness center but it is neither free nor part of the Venetian Hotel. It is an outside vendor. Overall, it is a great hotel if you take advantage of their package suite. We stayed Labor Day week for a 7 night stay + tax, total cost $800.00 with the suite package.	
