Oct 8 2009 	Excellent Hotel	We stayed in the Venetian 9/28/09 to 10/2/09 and it is wonderful. The room was very clean and well maintained. The staff were polite and efficient, including quick service at check-in. As with most of the big name hotels in Las Vegas, this hotel is massive. The entrance and passage way to the casino is so large you could fit many, many houses in it. The architecture is amazing, especially the frescos on the walls and ceilings. There were only three complaints I have. (1) They put a scent in the hotel ventilation system that frankly smells a bit like bathroom scent. I would rather have nothing, not even if it was a different scent. (2) The pool area chairs are reserved by hotel occupants by around 11:00 AM. I think it is discourteous, but that doesn't change anything. It still happens so be aware of it. The way the hotel is situated, only part of the pool area gets sun until mid afternoon so if you want sun as we did, you have to get there early. (3) Finally, fancy hotels have fancy prices. You pay high prices for the drinks and eats when ordering them at the pool. If you just want a non-alcoholic beverage, there is a Walgreens at the end of the block between the Venetian and the Palazzo which has much better prices and snacks too. It's a matter of judgment whether it is worth the money. My wife and I are people who like to stay in four and five star hotels. We stayed at Treasure Island across the street from the Venetian the past two times and I found it every bit as comfortable for my needs. We paid $159 a night this time when we could have stayed at Treasure Island for $99 a night. Nevertheless, we wanted to try the Venetian. I don't regret staying here, but I probably won't come back for the money spent.	
