rand are really friendly and a breath of fresh air compared to the Venetian's.Overall, it's a very good hotel. The canal and shopping complex is very impressive, as are the range of bars and restaurants. The Venetian is also linked underground to the Palazzo, so you can explore both easily. For non-smokers, the air conditioning in the casino is so advanced that you rarely notice the smoke, unlike some of the other casinos we visited. I'd also recommend doing a helicoptor tour with Maverick tours (booked through the hotel), it was really good fun.	
