Sep 27 2009 	Amazing Beautiful Gorgeous Hotel 	My husband and I chose to stay at The Venetian, Las Vegas as part of our honeymoon last year and it was amazing. We arrived at the hotel at night after a stretch Hummer tour along the strip. All of the hotels looked amazing but The Venetian definately stood out for us. After taking in all of the strip in one go we realised that The Venetian was very central and there were plenty of other hotels all within easy walking distance.We booked the standard suite but it was absolutely amazing, the bed was massive and there was a huge sunken sitting area looking out the window onto the strip. The bathroom was huge too, it had a shower, seperate bath and toilet then double sinks and a dressing table with mirror and lights around it (very Hollywood!). We got slippers, dressing gowns and other little bits'n' bobs (all gorgeously packagaged) which I love in a room. The room was so opulent - I loved it!The shopping area is gorgeous and the gondola ride along the canal is great and lovely to watch - plenty of singing going on! There are plenty of resturants to choose from, we liked the Grand Lux Cafe as it was quite informal, on the casino floor (great for people watching) and is open until very late. There was a vast menu and everything we tried was delicious. It's sister restaurant 'The Cheesecake Factory' is a must too! We have been back to Vegas again since our honeymoon and although we stayed elsewhere this time we returned to our favourite casino game at 'The Venetian'. We tried other games in different hotels but realised that the staff at 'The Venetian' were much friendlier and eager to help beginners. We also found that the actual casino floor was much lighter and brighter than many of the other casinos. My only downside to 'The Venetian' is the pool area. It is a stunning patio area with numerous pools but it is on a roof of one of the buildings. I burn easily and struggled to find any shade at all apart from the shadow of another building which moved as the sun moved round. Luckily the pool was quiet so I was able to move sun loungers easily. I did ask about parasols as I saw some scattered around which people were using. The attendant sid that I could have one if I saw a free one but they only had 5 for the whole of the hotel! I realise that the pool is perhaps not the reason why people visit Vegas but it did influence our decison of where to stay the second time as we knew we wanted to relax by the pool in the day.Overall, Las Vegas is amazing and The Venetian is stunning! We will be returning to both.	
