Sep 17 2009 	Amazing stay at the Venetian	Stayed at the Venetian from 9/13-9/16. The whole experience we had was simply amazing. We stayed in a Bella View Suite, which had a semi-decent view of the strip, but more of a view over the pool areas of the Venetian/Palazzo. The rooms were very spacious and well appointed and were simply gorgeous in every way, shape and form. We got very lucky at check-in on Sunday, because we only had to wait in line for about 3 minutes. Later during the day, I noticed that there were over 100+ people waiting to check in, so I could see how some people could complain about the check-in queue. The location of the Venetian is perfect, because it is close to everything and the Monorail boards @ Harrah's/IP etc. . .) However, in regards to gambling, I found myself only to be lucky at the Venetian! Not only was the gambling good, but the drink service is off the charts. You can get any free cocktail while gambling made with top shelf liquor( we had grey goose white russians and patron margaritas on the rocks). This is the only casino that treated me well on the entire trip!!! We got our room for ~$150 per night, which is a great deal and I would highly recommend staying at this hotel if you can get a room at &lt;$200/night. The only negative that I can think of was that the battery was low on the in-suite safe, so it took a little bit of time to lock our money up.P.S. The &quot;perfume smell&quot; of the hotel was not over-bearing to us, I actually liked how it masked the smell of any lingering cigarette smoke.	
