Aug 30 2009 	Definately a 5 Star Hotel	My fiance and I recently traveled to Vegas for a long weekend. We have been to Vegas before and stayed at Treasure Island. We opted for the Tower Suite at Treasure Island and weren't disappointed. However, for those of you who are familiar with the hotels on the strip, the venetian is almost directly across the street from Treasure Island. It caught our eye so when we decided to head back out to vegas we decided to try the venetian. This resort is definately 5 Stars from the staff to the room. We usually like to get the &quot;upper tier&quot; rooms in hotels where ever we stay but our basic room at the Venetian was better than some of the nicest rooms we stayed at other hotels. This resort was clean, the rooms... well even the basic room took our breath away. We liked the air freshner they must have put through the vents. The location is nice, its convenient to most other attractions on the strip but still quiet. The only draw back to this resort is that it is very expensive. Long island ice teas were 12 bucks a pop but were great. The nice thing about being expensive is that it excludes some of the other people you really don't want to be bunking next to. Tip: if you're not all about gambling take day trips. Las Vegas is a great starting point for a bunch of short drives to some great places. We went to Lake Havasu, AZ (beautiful drive), Death Valley, and Area 51 (definately get an Alien Burger at the Lil Ale' Inn. Something quirky but still a lot of fun.	
