Aug 29 2009 	Venetian great hotel! Way better than Bellagio!	My stay at the Venetian was top notch. We were treated first class as soon as we arrived to the hotel from the airport. Staff took care of our bags as we were directed to the line for checking. Although a long snaking line was infront of us we were at the counter in a matter of minutes. We asked for a room in the Venetian tower (More modern decor than the Venezia) that was as high as possible and close to the elevators (nothing worse than being on the outside of the builiding and having to hoof it to and from the elevator every time you need to leave your room). We got a room on the 24th floor only three doors from the center cooridor (and no we could not hear the elevators at all). Although we did not pay extra for a strip view room we did get a nice partial view.The room was amazing. Large, beautifully decorated, very comfortable bed. One of my best sleeps on vacation! We did most breakfasts at the Grand Lux Cafe just a few steps from the elevators on the main floor. They have a wonderful Express Breakfast for $15 that has lots of choices (Omlettes, baked goods, cereal, fruit, coffee and juice included) that was all you can eat. A very good value. We also the shows at the Venetian seeing the Phantom and Jersey Boys (Palazzo). I would recommend both to anyone.The question I always get asked? How did it stack up to the Bellagio? I would recommend the Venetian without hesitation. I've stayed in both the Venetian and Bellagio within 3 months of each other and found the Venetian far superior. The Bellagio public areas are always so crowded with gawking tourists that always seem to be in the way. The Bellagio rooms, although very nice, were not of the same luxury as the Venetian. Also, the shows offered at the Venetian/Palazzo are second to none... It was so nice not having to travel up and down the strip to take in such wonderful entertainment.If given the choice, try the Venetian. You'll be glad you did!	
