Aug 27 2009 	Great fun !	This was our first trip to Vegas and so elected to stay in what we thought would be a luxury hotel and we were not mistaken.Check in was fairly simple - took about 20 minutes - we were allocated a room on the 25th floor with a view of the strip - however when we opened the curtains the first thing we saw were two cranes and a building site...not what we expected at all !We called to the reception and after explaining that we had booked a room with a view of the strip they sent a bellboy up with a key for an alternative room....however this turned out to be on the 10th floor with an even worse view than before (I think the staff may not all be aware of the location of the rooms). I then had to go back to reception where a very pleasant staff member (with a floor plan) found a room with a view of the strip and not an oppressive view of construction) on the 24th floor.If this construction is going to be there for a while the hotel management should take a look at what is done in Venice when unsightly construction work is in progress....they put up a decorated tarpauline which for all intents and purposes completely transforms the view - and it would no doubt make the receptionists jobs a lot easier...and the guest experience much more pleasant. The room itself was spacious with a seating area, work desk, 3 flat screen tv's and a great bathroom (no fighting over who was going to shower first !). We had a great king size bed which was very comfortable and we slept great without any disturbance from guests on the same floor. Fairly peaceful. A nice touch was the electronic controls for the curtains and roman blinds. There was a charge for internet connection in the room whilst it was available free of charge in the public areas - don't quite understand the logic of that as anyone could walk in and use free whilst paying guests had to pay to use it in their rooms - very inconvenient especially for people living in different time zones ???The on-site facilities are amazing....the shopping area with canal and gondola rides running through it and a permanent feeling of dusk was very relaxing and really meant there was no need to leave the hotel unless you wanted a change of scenery.The swimming pool area had lots of sunbeds although most were laid out so you felt you were one large shared bed !! Luckily we managed to find beds with some space on either side which were better. The pool reception staff were very good and explained where everything was which was a nice touch. We had breakfast in the poolside restaurant one morning (eggs with chorizo was very tasty but at 17$ not cheap). My husband asked for more toast and after about 10 minutes was told &quot;so sorry, we can't provide that as the mobile toaster has been moved to another restaurant in the hotel - ???&quot; He was however provided with some bread. Very strange response for this level of hotel......We asked for some herbal tea...which they did not have .....so asked just for a cup of hot water ...and was astonished to find a 0.25 cent charge on the bill.......The waitress poolside service was welcome and the mojitos went down very well...There was a lot of interest in the Tao section of the pool with queues to get in most days and the Tao restaurant at night was jam packed. It was fun watching the shapes and posturing of the girls and boys in the queue.!!Quite liked the Duelling Pianos (which was a new concept to us) We received 50$ slot credits and restaurant discount vouchers upon arrival which were useful although a 30 minute queue to convert the slot credit to a Club Grazie card was a bit much...Overall a great stay...the hotel location is perfect and within a stroll of the show at Treasure Island, the Bellagio Fountains and across the road from the Mirage Volcano....also Cesares Palace offers an alternative shopping experience.Walked down to the Stratosphere but found that end of the strip was not as enticing....Make sure to pay a visit to the Fremont Experience...it was great fun and a highlight of our trip !All in all...well worth staying at this hotel and we look forward to returning soon.	
