Aug 24 2009 	Fantastic	I stayed at the Venetian for a few days after a work conference at the Mandalay Bay resort and I must say I was impressed. In Vegas 5 star doesn't really mean 5 stars, but then again they are not charging 5 star prices either. So that in mind I think the Venetian offers a great value with a bit of luxury thrown in. Service is ok, quite impersonal and a bit slow but with hotel this size I think it's not unexpected. The room is nice and spacious with a sunken lounge area, perfect for hanging out with friends before or after a big night out. Bed was very comfortable. The bathroom is brilliant! It's really big with two sinks a bath tub and a gigantic shower cubicle that could easily fit in 4 people, fluffy bathrobes and slippers are also available in the room. The toilet is separate. Pool area is lovely and doesn't get overly crowded like some other hotel pools on the strip.I ordered room service breakfast on the first day. It took almost an hour to arrive and was quite expensive, so having wisened up I just went out for breakfast after that. I will definitely stay at the Venetian again.	
