Aug 24 2009 	Stunning room	As with most hotels in LV, The Venetian is simply vast. The bedrooms are probably the best we have ever stayed in and the beds the most comfortable. Extremely spacious and well equipped - apart from the irritating but growing habit of not providing tea and coffee making facilities in the bedrooms. Also, the minibar is stuffed with overpriced goodies that are electronically tagged - so, even just moving them to put your own things in incurs a charge. Housekeeping was excellent, front desk and concierge good too but try and avoid the principal booking-in times when you can queue for half an hour. Starbucks and other restaurants in the foyer. Location is great, Phantom is showing (excellent) in the hotel theatre and Cirque du Soleil is just next door at the Wynn. You can even take a Gondola ride outside - cheesy but why not - this is Vegas after all. Try and get Strip facing rooms.	
