Aug 9 2009 	The Venetian is not just a hotel but an experience	To finish our &quot;fly-drive&quot; holiday to California and Las Vegas we decided to stay somewhere special and &quot;The Venetian&quot; did not disappoint.This is probably the best large-scale hotel we have ever stayed in from the opulent reception area with it's fountain and frescoes to the huge suites with their lounge, huge beds and marble bathrooms. The swimming pools are large and beautifully designed giving the impression of a Roman baths rather than hotel pools and the evening pool is lovely being lit up for an evening dip at night. The public and pool areas are sumptious and spotlessly clean and coupled with the hot climate make this an amazing place to stay.The Gondola rides are really worth doing although we'd recommend that you pre-book in the evenings to avoid disappointment as the rides do get fully booked. The Gondoliers are nice and friendly and make the experience really pleasant.Walking around &quot;St Mark's Square&quot; the painted ceiling really seems alive with the clouds appearing to move as you walk - truly an amazing place.We were also impressed with the restaurants and bars as we were not really too bothered about gambling and found them to be both lavish and up-to-date.For those who want to shop there are fashion outlets everywhere although the prices were high compared to UK prices.Outside the hotel, the replica &quot;Campanile&quot; and &quot;Doges Palace&quot; are beautifully recreated and when lit up at night offer a spectacular sight.We thought that we would find Las Vegas slightly &quot;tacky&quot; but the thought, effort and huge amount of investment that has gone into the hotels in this area and the Venetian in particular really wins you over.Las Vegas is an amazing place and the Venetian is the very best place to stay and enjoy the experience, being probably one of the best hotels anywhere in the world.	
