Jul 28 2009 	A nice stay	We stayed in a &quot;Venezia Bella View Suite&quot; Saturday and Sunday nights. Overall it was a pleasant stay, and we enjoyed the Venetian quite a bit. On the upside: -------------------A) The interior of the combined Pallazo/Venetian is very nice. There are numerous places to shop/entertain/dine within the complex, and it is a very pleasant (if not a bit Disneyland-ish) environment. The hotel service was good, timely, and friendly. B) The room was well appointed, spacious, and very comfortable. C) Tons of good dining options abound in the Ventian/Pallazo. On the downside: -------------------1) Going anywhere is a real effort. Leaving your Venezia suite involves **a lot** of walking and a chain of elevators. The walking distances to go anywhere are just absurd. I'd swear I walked less when I worked in downtown San Francisco taking public transit everywhere. 2) The hotel info lists the Venezia pool as a private pool for Venezia tower guests. There's nothing private about it. Anyone can go there. During our stay the pool deck wasn't overcrowded though. I suspect that it doesn't get overrun by outsiders because of the afore-mentioned walking distances and chain of elevators. The pool area is nice, but it is misleading to refer to it as private. 3) Hotel checkin at the Venetian is grossly understaffed, and the directions for Venezia guests are incorrect. When I arrived, there was a checkin line that looked like a line for Space Mountain. There were at least 100 people in the line. As I scanned the area and began to seethe in anger, I noticed the signs that directed Venezia tower guests to another lobby. After a bit of a walk and an elevator ride to get there, I found an empty lobby with a concierge who politely told me to go back downstairs; that Venezia checkin was combined with Venitian checkin. I almost lost it. I asked the concierge if she really expected me to stand in the ridiculous check in line. She recommended I go to a &quot;special&quot; line. I did, and there was one person in front of me. From there, check in was snappy. BEWARE though... if you are a Ventian guest, be prepared for an abusive checkin wait. The line was full nearly every time I walked past it during my stay. 4) My room type was a &quot;Venzia Bella View Suite.&quot; The view was of the air conditioner fans and the McCarran Airport. Yay! There are 6 possible views, 5 of which are decent. I had the crap one.	
