Jul 24 2009 	Customer Service at its Finest	We arrived at The Venetian 10hours prior to our scheduled check in time. We were greeted by a bell hop with a smile and was asked if we would like to check our bags untill we were able to check in to the hotel. She then told us that we should probably go through the check in line because the hotel often allows early check ins as rooms become available. I would definately reccommend for anyone who arrives early to try this, from what I hear they will call you as soon as one becomes available for you. We actually got lucky and there was one waiting for us. The queue to check in was only 3 partys deep when we got in line but by the time we had checked in it was backed up pretty far. When we got up to our rooms we were amazed. All the pictures do not give this place justice. Our room was pretty clean except for this one sticky spot in the toilet room that my wife couldnt avoid. I tried cleaning it myself with a towel and some water but it just wouldnt come up! Everything else was immaculate and I felt very comfortable with how well everything was maintained. About 5 minutes into being in our room we heard a single knock at the door and a man from houskeeping barged in he apologized profusely when he saw us in the room, apparently it was just a quality inspection of the cleaning service. Within 5 more minutes of the first knock we heard another one and this time a woman came in for the same reason. We then put the security latch on the door as to avoid any other confusion. After another 5 minutes we heard knocking for a third time and this time it was the bell hop with our baggage. This was nice becouse we didnt want to spend our whole morning in our room.We found all the other ammenities this hotel offered to be top notch if not alittle pricey. I would highly recommend the Razul Ceremony at the Canyon Ranch Spa for all the serious couples or married folks like myself. My wife and I got very intimate in there and it would be one of the hottest experiences of your life, well worth the $200 for 1 hour. I also recommend the couples massage. Nothing great as far as massages go but it was relaxing and you can enjoy the other co ed enviroments the spa has to offer for free afterwards. Pool was nice not overly crowded but we went in the morning. After noon can get pretty noisy due to the club enviroment of Tao Beach. It was like 112 degrees during our stay and we where offered an umbrellas almost as soon as we sat down.As far as restraunts I would not recommend Dos Caminos I simply did not like the food. They do have this awsome tequila tasting on the drinks menu.... that was definately good haha! Grand Lux Cafe is good for a value meal and the food courts in both the casino and the shopping area are good. If your interested in some fine dining Cut, Valentino's. and Aquanox are all excellent but pricey. One quam with the food faire, weres the buffet?!?! We had to walk over to the Wynn to eat at one. Overall a good experience, when we called the concierge to get reservations or tickets we always got what we wanted withing a few minutes. Blue Man Group was awsome.The best part of this trip I think were the comps which we got about $550 worth taken off our bill at the end. Ive never had this happen to me but then again I never knew to ask for them. Im no high roller but I would definately say that if your not bringing $500-1000 a day for entertainment, food, and gambling then your probably in the wrong place. Stay somewhere were you can have more fun enjoying your moneys worth and were youll be more appreciated.	
