Jun 29 2009 	Beautiful room and great room service	We spent two days at the Venetian after our wedding in the Grand Canyon and a very serious butt kicking honeymoon of hiking and climing.When we got to the hotel we just wanted to relax in luxury and thats exactly what it offered. Beautiful huge suite, great room service, pretty nice spa, great location. I am more of a B and B, or boutique hotel or historic hotel lover, but we definitly enjoyed ourselves. We just had a couple hours after all of our spa-ing to check out the strip, so being at the Venetian offered an awesome prime location to hit all of the hotspots.	
Jun 28 2009 	Loved this place	Venetian was 5 star all the way. We had no problem with service. Pool area was very nice. What I liked about this hotel is I did not have to walk through the casino to get a coffee in the morning. Coffee and pastrie place was right by the elevators. Nice and convienient. Also the pool was on the 4th floor and you did not have to go through the casino to get to it like some of the other hotels we have stayed at. The rooms were beautiful. We did not touch anything in the fridge because as said before if you even touch the stuff it will send message down to the front desk that you have used it. Everything is on sensors. There is a ABC drugstore on the front of the hotel on the strip were you can pick up pop and snacks. I paid 3.50 for flavoured water at the hotel and at ABC it was 1.99. We truly loved this hotel and will be back.	
Jun 27 2009 	A Very Massive and beautiful place to stay	I &quot;heard&quot; the Venetian is the largest resort/hotel in the world. After staying there for a week I would say, if it isn't, I don't want to see the largest. It is impressive in size, service, and amenities, but plan on getting lost. I heard someone try to use their key to enter my room late one night. No worries, I thought, I have done the same thing. A few minutes later house keeping tried to enter my room, but thank goodness I had the door latched. I assume, because it would have been so far to get to the front desk, and it being close to 2 am, this person called and house keeping used their master key to help this person get entry. The door did open, the latch caught, and I heard an accented, &quot;I'm sorry.&quot; The exercise facility is as impressive as the casino. The shopping plaza/mall is something to experience. I couldn't affort to shop there, but it was extremely well done. If someone else was paying I would stay here again. The rooms are large and the beds are comfortable. With my own money I don't thing I would pay for a room here and then make my normal contributions to Vegas at the same time.	
Jun 27 2009 	Romantic Get Away	We reserved the Venetian as part of a package through Alaskan Airlines. Our stay was from Mon-Wed. Check in was quick and efficient. We were offered upgrades to a more spacious suite, we did not accept, and did not feel pressured. Instead we stayed with the &quot;standard room&quot; which was anything but standard. Our suite was absolutely beautiful and very comfortable. The bathroom was luxurious and the toilitries were delightful. Whether it was the housekeeping, conceirge, or waitress, all staff was attentive and we had a wonderful time. The only concern/suggestion to fellow travelers is the hotel does not provide a list of items charged upon check out (most hotels slide this information under your door). Instead you have to get in line and make a request. We did not have time to do this and opted for &quot;express check-out&quot; which made me a little nervous. However, this did not deter from our stay and we would go back to this hotel again. Last note, I've read some reveiws regarding children in Las Vegas. Las Vegas is a place for adults and is not recommended for children.	
