Jun 25 2009 	A good place to stay in Vegas	We stayed at the venetian for 5 nights. At the time, the price was very reasonable for what we got from the hotel. The rooms and facilities are incredible, just like most of the hotels in Vegas, and the Casino and the food court were OK, nothing special. The services could be better. The only setback happened when we left the hotel. We checked out from the hotel, paid our expenses and when we got back to Brazil my credit card bill came with almost 100 dollars in beverages that we did not drink at all. Anyway, besides that, we had a great experience.	
