Jun 25 2009 	You wont get better value for money	I have just returned from my first trip to vegas, I can not get over what you get for your money, I stayed at the Venetian hotel and booked through lowcostlasvegas.com, they were doing a special offer on a stay of 4 nights or more. This hotel had everything, it was ideally located on the strip, food was good in the restaurants and the check in very slick. I would recommend this to anyone, I think they have so many big hotels in Vegas that they must be trying to shift rooms as for the same money you would have a job to stay in a Travellodge in the UK!	
Jun 24 2009 	The best combination of a classy and beautiful hotel filled with Vegas-style attraction	I was blown away with the beauty of the Venetian from the suites to the public rooms. The restaurants were lovely and modern and even the casino was pretty. The meeting rooms and ballrooms were fabulous too. The staff were professional and very accomodating and did a fabulous job of hosting our company's annual event. The only two areas for improvement would be the overuse of fragrance used in certain areas of the building and some of the hotel-catered food choices. For a sensative nose, some areas within the hotel were overly fragrant. Also, some of the food items catered were underwhelming. The actual restaurants were terrific though. I would reccommend this resort for any personal trip or company-sponsored event. I would definately stay there again.	
